bib.abstract: Supercritical carbon dioxide (sCO2) cycles are gaining attention for their efficiency and low carbon footprint in power plants. This study focuses on optimizing the performance of a 5 MW simple recuperated sCO2 Brayton loop during inventory control, a recommended strategy for maximum part-load efficiencies.
